2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |   # Fix: Correctly escape non-BMP characters in AsciiJSON
2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |   ## Summary
2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |   `render.AsciiJSON` previously corrupted non-BMP Unicode characters (e.g., emoji) by generating malformed `\u` escapes that contained more than four hex digits. This violated the JSON specification, leading to silent data corruption upon decoding. This PR updates `AsciiJSON` to correctly encode non-BMP characters as UTF-16 surrogate pairs, ensuring proper round-tripping of all Unicode data.
2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |   ## Changes
2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |   *   Modified `render/json.go`, specifically the `AsciiJSON.Render` method.
2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |   *   Updated the Unicode escaping logic for runes greater than `unicode.MaxASCII`:
2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |       *   BMP characters (U+0000 to U+FFFF) are now correctly escaped using a single `\uXXXX` sequence.
2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |       *   Non-BMP characters (U+10000 and above) are now correctly converted into UTF-16 surrogate pairs and then escaped as two `\uXXXX\uXXXX` sequences.
2026-06-04 13:34:32,346 | DEBUG    |   *   Increased the pre-allocated buffer `escapeBuf` size from 6 to 12 bytes to accommodate the longer surrogate pair escapes.
2026-06-04 13:34:32,347 | DEBUG    |   
2026-06-04 13:34:32,347 | DEBUG    |   ## Test plan
2026-06-04 13:34:32,347 | DEBUG    |   Verified using the minimal reproducible example provided in the issue description:
2026-06-04 13:34:32,347 | DEBUG    |   1.  Encoded a `map[string]string` containing a non-BMP character (e.g., `{"msg": "😀"}`) using `render.AsciiJSON`.
2026-06-04 13:34:32,347 | DEBUG    |   2.  Observed that the output now correctly uses a UTF-16 surrogate pair (`{"msg":"\ud83d\ude00"}`).
2026-06-04 13:34:32,347 | DEBUG    |   3.  Confirmed that `json.Unmarshal` of this output now correctly decodes back to the original non-BMP character (`😀`), ensuring data integrity and round-trip consistency.
2026-06-04 13:34:32,347 | DEBUG    |   
